    <briefdescription>
<para>Properties defining how text should be drawn on screen. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>`DrawProperties` encapsulates the positioning and styling information needed to render text at a specific location with a specific font.</para>
<para>## Properties</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>**fontId:** Identifies which loaded font family to use.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>**position:** Screen-space coordinates (x, y) for the text origin.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>**scale:** Multiplier for the text size (1.0 = original size).</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>## Example</para>
<para>```cpp <ref refid="structhelios_1_1rendering_1_1text_1_1DrawProperties" kindref="compound">DrawProperties</ref> props{ .fontId = FontId{1}, .position = {100.0f, 200.0f}, .scale = 1.5f }; ```</para>
